_sText:
ze_13 - Was the save file but liked the name so kept it.
A zombie escape map based on a mix of running and holding.

How to play - Add players and that's it.

No horrible clipping.

No over powered weapons to stop zombies.

No zombie blockers.

No real way for them annoying team mates to kill you or get you trapped.

No cheap teleports to save campers, you either escape or die.

It's a fair map based around the players doing the work, working together and over comming the challanage.
If I could control it I would have the zombies winning this map more then the cts, no challange in the game if as a ct you win non stop.

If you want to run to the end of the map and set off the nuke without seeing a single zombie or go and find a secret weapon that unbalances the map behond playable, fun conditions, then I think this isn't the map for you !


64 Spawns.

Average FSP 350 (ATI HD5670 512mb, AMD7850 2GB DDR2 666MHZ 
RAM- 19" LCD)

Optimized.

Compiled on NORMAL using valves compiler.

Cubemaps compiled.

AFK/SPAWN CAMPING killer after 60 seconds of the games round.

Flashlights are disabled due to a dark room.

Teleports parented to the elevators so people wont be bugged in to the brush work.

Zombie friendly triggers that enable walk ways and break blockades.

Random breakable items at the safe zone, 1 per round so it can make the safe zone a little more difficult to protect.

No known bugs.


I hope people enjoy it and that's its fun !

From ZeMotanumInc, ZeApertureScience, ZeSurfFcility, spMainFour, kothApertureScience_III comes...

Ze Surf Facility V2.3
==================
You escape from the Zombies, but there is no running only surfing! Well, there is some running, here and there.
------------------

New in V2.3
- Nerfed the ending to 1 minute from 1.5 minutes
- Added song to the map. No more akward silence
- Other minor changes

**Features** 

- Tutorial Level 

- Automatic Surf Settings 

- Supports mode where zombie is not sent back to spawn 

- AFK killer

- Noob friendly, retry and move up if you fail. No fall damage 

- A whole new stage! Racing! 

- 3 stages not including tutorial to surf 

- 18 different combinations with the randomized stage selection 

- Lighted map! 

- 6 minutes of pure adrenaline 

- Surf Boards -First zombies to finish the final stage get 15k hp!

- Teamwork and communication required!

**NOTE**, as with any map, you can't please everyone. Just upload it and give it a try! You won't regret it! As you learn the map, and get better at surfing it will become more enjoyable and more fun!

Sorry for the delay, but I guess is better late than never! This is probably my last Ze map, as I am moving on with other projects, but I just wanted to finish this up for everyone in the community to enjoy!

I might re-compile my maps for CS:GO if a zombie mod becomes available.

Developed by Eugenio 'Motanum' Roman

Bugs, comments, suggestions to agent_2114@hotmail.com or eugenio.motanum91@gmail.com

See screenshots

**Installation**, just paste the all of the files in the rar on your maps folder for counter strike source Default should be Files\Steam\steamapps\Account_Name\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps

**Note**, zeApertureScienceOB got trashed because of ported models, if you want the map for your server just pm for a link to mediafire

After many months of work and after understaning how hannibal made this huge map i can present to you a hopefully working version of his
greatest, largest and last map.

Based on a post-apocalyptic future where the last remains of the 
humanity will activate the final device for killing all zombies around the globe.
Four stages, four generators. The humans objective: activate all the generators and
defend the main core in the fifth stage.
The map tries to keep the shape and gameplay of the classic maps:

  • No mass teleports to force players to move ahead.
  • No invisible walls.
  • All ways are connected with no teleports.
  • Wide paths
  • Intense action due the lack of helps to the human team The map, although, includes modern maps features.
  • Human items (stages 2,4,5)
  • Zombie items (stage 3,5)
  • Stages system
  • Extreme mode
  • Player controlled boss
  • Event system

Event system: 
Hidden and visible events may be triggered by players
during the stages 1,2,3 and 4. These will alter the gameplay in the stage 5 and will determine how easy or difficult will be to defend the core and save the humanity.

Extreme:
Extreme difficult will be enabled after stage 5 is completed.
Completing extreme difficulty will be considered completing the map at 100%

Infected Tramway V2.1
===================
By Eugenio “Motanum” Roman
------------------
### Key Info

From the creator of Motanum Inc, Surf Facility, Motanum’s Main Four and more, comes the continuation to Motanum Inc. After escaping Motanum Inc, the army has an assignment for you. Obtain the coordinates to a rocket launch pad to escape Earth and the nasty infection! A very vanilla zombie escape map. Visit a facility on a mountain and try to survive the zombies behind you. Requiring team work and skills, the map is definitely a must have on your server.

### User Manual
Simply run and hold when you should defend. Sometimes a player needs to activate a monitor or key, this is shown by having a green glow. Green glow means it must be pressed, default key is E. Red glow means it is locked and something must be done to unlock the button. If there is no glow, it is of little interest. To obtain the plans/coordinates simply walk to the table. A trigger will fire the events that will enable you to continue. This should allow players to keep pushing regardless the weapon glitch. The admin room is next, just before the plans. There is a window into it and the 4 options are available. On choosing a difficulty the game will restart by killing everyone.

### V3 Changes
- Nerfing the octagon to 1 on easy, 2 on normal, 4 on hard and 6 on suicide
- Changed secrets to p90 with UNLIMITED ammo! Nice light following you now with a use!
- Changed the stair hold out to make it easier to defend
- Added nades near the final healing spot to provide with extra tools for humans
- Music is now affected by the Music slides! Hate my songs? mute it!
- Added a paypal sign at the start for those warm hearth-ed fellows!
- Fixed the voice acting lines not being packed into the map! It NOW has actual voice acting! Experience a story unfold as you survive!
- Fixed a bug in which suicide mode would not be executed after finishing hard mode.

### Features

- Optimized map
- 4 difficulties, changing the way you defend!
- Admin room to select a difficulty
- Waiting for players time! The map restarts after 20 seconds on load, to give players a chance to join in.
- HDR lighting. The apocalypse has never been this pretty
- Up to 72 player spots
- 6 and a half minutes of fun time!
- Massive detailed level
- Random octagon gates
- Voice acting by Michichael Folsune
- Story guided level
- Exciting Locations
- And more!
- Future updates!

This will be my last zombie escape map for CSS, I will return with more if CSGO gets zombie escape mod. I love maping for Zombie escape, but I have other big proyects! So check out my website for updates. https://sites.google.com/site/motanumproyect/

### Special thanks
- Michichael Folsune for lending me his voice. It really adds to the atmosphere. 
- Bill Hawken was the lab rat when I was playing with the idea of voice acting. 
- Seaotter and dota2.ca for their donations and motivations.
- Zeph, Enviolinator and Kaemon for their entity knowledge. Without it, I couldn't upgrade the map to its current state
- Unreal, Layerba714 and Mevious for running through my map

### Final Words
Map developed by Eugenio 'Motanum' Roman Bugs, comments, suggestions to eugenio.motanum91@gmail.com. More maps from me to come. See screenshots for a visual idea. Don’t forget to download and rate! 

### Installation
Just paste the all of the files in the rar on your maps folder for counter strike source. Default should be Files\Steam\steamapps\Account_Name\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps

_sText:
*Update; Well... I would like to say this will be the last update, but as you can see that's been happening for a while now. This update aims to improve the game play of the level by making it easier for humans in certain areas.

.Gives more time for humans to get into the fort after boat ride.

.Harder for zombies to cut people off near tram area.

.Two shotguns added to fort. 

.Made it harder for humans to get onto the boat, this forces humans to be a tad more pro active and move. 

.Lots of little fixes.*

*Update; ok ok.... This is hopefully going to be the last update. This update fixes all missing sounds and music that did not get adding when I was using Pakrat...*

*Updated; this update is only for people with more than 62 player servers. All this patch does is increase the number of player spawns to fix problems some servers were having.*

Hi all, this is a big update for Grand Boat Escape. It comes in two versions, day time version set during the day, and night time version set during night time with a little lightening going on in the background. Both night time and day time versions come with the same amount of fixes and optimizations. 

The main improvement in this update is with the increase of fps. Overall there should be around 100-200 added fps what should smooth out everyone experience during play. There also a whole host of other features and bug fixes that should improve game play but also looks.

Sadly to improve the fps some visuals needed to be toned down but hopefully it will not be too noticeable when you guys are playing online.

**'Posted on older version, but still applies'**

This is Grand Boat Escape, its a massive update that took me a little while to do. It recreates tons of features within this map to improve game play and scenery. Overall, this map has been made to be MUCH harder, I felt that the older version out currently was way too easy and got boring very fast, but that should all change now with the amount of changes that has been added in version 3_6. Hope you guys/girls really like it.

If your interested in seeing what the old version looked like, go here: Grand Boat Escape

Added Feature List:

.More routs, this to hopefully give the player more power on witch way they go instead of just straight.

.Added boxes, they need to be jumped over by humans, but can be instantly be destroyed by zombies touching it. This is to slow the humans down and allow the zombies to catch up.

.Added douche bag doors, These doors can be permanently closed by a human. Thing is, they don't even block out zombies that well. I added them to block out other humans by slightly faster "trolly" individuals forcing the humans to take other routs.

.Greatly improved end fort, what has multiple layers and a Air Ship at the end that the humans must defend, and many more things.

.Changed the boat, hopefully will be better than the old one, It also allows the zombies to get in from the water, very hard though.

.Greatly improved the lighting and effects.

.3d Sky Box has now be finally added, this makes the map look much more larger.

.A lot of optimization has been done, to make way for all the improvements.

.In-proved sounds/music.

.and allot more! probably.

**Story**
=========
The map is based at the top research facility for genetic experimentation, high up in the hills of the Blue Mountains has been attacked.
The screams at the other end of the radio were horrendous. The Elevator was on lock down while the initial attack began, so your team was trapped on the lower floors of the facility, so you could do nothing but watch on the monitors as scientists and security guards were ripped apart by invisible creatures.

There is silence now. No one is left but your squad.

You are marines, you are strong, you are smart...you are being hunted....

**The mechanics of the map**
============================
There are 2 parts to the map. The topside, surrounded by hills with a house and a tool shed in the middle, then the underground complex where the research is done.
The marines have just made it through the service elevator onto the second floor after a 12 hours lock down.
There are creaks and groans that can be heard in the distance, as well as a faint sound that could be mistaken for an engine.

The marines must brave the corridors of the lab and have 2 ways to reach the surface (via an elevator or through the pipe work).

**Notes**
=========
This is the first map I have done that I incorporated soundscape scripts into the level. I have found they create a nice atmosphere and surrounding. For those of you who don't know what soundscapes are, they are background sounds that trigger when a player moves into the target radius (ie when walking from indoors to outdoors). The soundscape triggers and the player hears a variety of sounds, for example: The outdoor area of this map is raining, so the primary soundscape is raining, but has wind howling, crickets etc in the background as well, where as inside, underground, you hear the humming sound of lab equipment.
For those of you who have never used them in your map, look at a tutorial and do it. Makes it so much more immersive.

I also had a bit more of a play around with cubemaps. They made the glass look at lot more solid and the reflective capabilities blend nice with the reflective floor. This is especially good when the lights are turned off and the backup power turns on.

**Story**
=========
We were escorting precious cargo through an undisclosed military trade route. While deep in the forest the convoy was ordered to stop.
The forest went silent. No howls from the winds or birds singing.
Then they attacked.
It all happened so fast. There were screams in all directions; torsos flying through the air.
We couldn't see the enemy, we could only hear their roars of satisfaction as each man was cut down where he stood.

We have managed to push them back, but our vehicles and radios have been damaged. 
It has started to rain now; lighting and thunder crashing through the sky.

We will not survive this.

**The mechanics of the map**
============================
There are few things to this map. The Marines start at the opposite end of the map to the predators. There are 3 weapon cache's filled with AK47s, M4A1s and P90s. There is also an awp and 2 m3's around the corps' of your fallen comrades.

There are a few high rise points in the map to make your final stand, as well as a cave leading from the marine spawn to the broken down bunker further up the track.

**Notes**
=========
The map is filled with tree and bush props and some uses my first ever custom displacement (was a good project to learn on).

There is also func_precipitation throughout the entire map causing heavy rain and some ambient generics and lights to cause a random thunder effect from 2 different sounds.

Finally, I have used soundscapes to create the atmosphere of a horrific storm both indoors and out.
